:INFO
The Most Beautiful Fantasy Novel I Have Read and the Problem With That
The Name of the Wind is the best-written fantasy novel I have encountered. Patrick \
Rothfuss has a prose style that makes the reading experience feel effortless and \
deliberate at the same time. Kvothe is a character I have not tired of rereading. \
The problem is that the trilogy is unfinished after fifteen years and no \
publication date exists for the third book. That fact has changed the way I \
feel about recommending it to people who have not started yet.

